level.abstract: Mos model level selector, set to 54 for HSPICE model. together with the keyword NMOS or PMOS specified in the model cards

paramchk.abstract: Switch for parameter value check. Default = 1.

binunit.abstract: Model parameter geometrical binning model selector. Default = 1;The other optional value is 0.

mtrlmod.abstract: Gate stack and substrate material model selector.  Default = 0 (Poly Si/oxide/Si MOSFETs);The other optional value is 1 (High-k and metal gates).

tempmod.abstract: Temperature-dependence model selector. Default = 0; The other optional values are 1, 2, and 3.

rdsmod.abstract: Bias-dependent LDD source/drain resistance model and topology selector. Default = 0 (Resistances are integrated into the channel current model formulation;  The other optional value is 1(the resistances are lumped into the source and drain diffusion resistances and connected between the internal and external source and drain nodes).

mobmod.abstract: Mobility model selector.  Default = 0. The other optional values are 1, 2, and 3.

wpemod.abstract: The well-proximity effect model. Default = 0;  The other optional value is 1.

l.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if (L + XL) is less than or equal to XGL.

sa.abstract: Distance of one gate edge to one LOD edge. Default = 0.0 in [m].

sb.abstract: Distance of the other gate edge to the other LOD edge. Default = 0.0 in [m].

sc.abstract: Distance from the gate edge to the edge of the well. Default = 0.0 in [m].
sc.notice: A warning message will be issued if it is less than zero and it will be reset to zero when WPEMOD is set to 1.

sd.abstract: Spacing between the edges of two adjacent gates of a multi-finger device. Default = 2.0*DMCG in [m].

sca.abstract: Integral of the first-order photoresist-scattered dopant distribution function. Default = 0.0.
sca.notice: A warning message will be issued if it is less than zero and it will be reset to zero when WPEMOD is set to 1.

scb.abstract: Integral of the second-order photoresist-scattered dopant distribution function. Default = 0.0.
scb.notice: A warning message will be issued if it is less than zero and it will be reset to zero when WPEMOD is set to 1.

scc.abstract: Integral of the third-order photoresist-scattered dopant distribution function. Default = 0.0.
scc.notice: A warning message will be issued if it is less than zero and it will be reset to zero when WPEMOD is set to 1.

toxe.abstract: (Equivalent) electrical gate oxide thickness. Default = 30.0 ¡Á 10^-10 in [m].
toxe.notice: If it is not positive, a fatal error message will be issued. When MTRLMOD = 1, it is EOT.

toxm.abstract: Target (equivalent) electrical gate oxide thickness at which the BSIM4 model parameters are extracted. Default = TOXE in [m].
toxm.notice: If it is not positive, a fatal error message will be issued.

toxp.abstract: (Equivalent) physical gate oxide thickness. Default = TOXE in [m].
toxp.notice: If it is not positive, a fatal error message will be issued. When MTRLMOD = 1, it is computed by BSIM4 automatically.

toxref.abstract: The target gate oxide/dielectric layer thickness for the gate direct-tunneling model [refer to the chapter on the gate-direct tunneling current model]. Default = 30.0 ¡Á 10^-10 in [m].
toxref.notice: If it is not positive, a fatal error message will be issued.

dtox.abstract: The difference between TOXE and TOXP. Default = 0.0 in [m].
dtox.notice: If it is not equal to the difference between TOXE and TOXP, it will be ignored by BSIM4.

eot.abstract: Equivalent oxide thickness of the gate dielectric layer for MTRLMOD = 1. Default = 15.0 ¡Á 10^-10 in [m].
eot.notice: If it is not positive, a fatal error message will be issued.

vddeot.abstract: The power supply voltage for the gate voltage at which EOT is extracted from measured gate capacitance when MTRLMOD = 1. Default = 1.5 for NMOS and -1.5 for PMOS in [V].
vddeot.notice: If it is not positive, a fatal error message will be issued.

tempeot.abstract: The temperature at which TOXP is extracted from EOT when MTRLMOD = 1. Default = 300.15 in [Kelvin].

leffeot.abstract: The effective channel length at which TOXP is extracted from EOT when MTRLMOD = 1. Default = 1.0 ¡Á 10^-6 in [m].

weffeot.abstract: The effective channel width at which TOXP is extracted from EOT when MTRLMOD = 1. Default = 10.0 ¡Á 10^-6 in [m].

epsrox.abstract: Relative dielectric constant of the gate dielectric layer for MTRLMOD = 0. Default = 3.9.
epsrox.notice: If it is less than 0.0, a fatal error message will be issued.

epsrsub.abstract: Relative dielectric constant of the substrate for MTRLMOD = 1. Default = 11.7.
epsrsub.notice: If it is less than 0.0, a fatal error message will be issued.

epsrgate.abstract: Relative dielectric constant of the gate. If MTRLMOD = 0, the material is poly silicon. If it is zero, a metal gate is impliedand no gate depletion will take place and be modeled. Default = 11.7.
epsrgate.notice: If it is less than 0.0, a fatal error message will be issued.

xl.abstract: Offset between designed and actual physical gate lengths due to mask/etch effect. Default = 0.0 in [m].
xl.notice: If it makes L physical less than XGL, a fatal error message will be issued.

xw.abstract: Offset between designed and actual physical gate widths due to mask/etch effect. Default = 0.0 in [m].

lint.abstract: Gate-source or -drain overlap length. Default = 0.0 in [m].

dlc.abstract: Gate-source or -drain overlap length for capacitance models. Default = LINT in [m].

wint.abstract: Gate and channel edge overlap length in the width direction. Default = 0.0 in [m].

dwc.abstract: Gate and channel edge overlap length in the width direction for capacitance models. Default = WINT in [m].

dwj.abstract: Gate and channel edge overlap length in the width direction for junction diode models. Default = DWC in [m].

ll.abstract: Coefficient of length dependence for LINT.

lw.abstract: Coefficient of width dependence for LINT.

lwl.abstract: Coefficient of length and width cross term dependence for LINT.

lln.abstract: Power of length dependence for LINT.

lwn.abstract: Power of width dependence for LINT.

llc.abstract: Coefficient of length dependence for DLC for capacitance models.

lwc.abstract: Coefficient of width dependence for DLC for capacitance models.

lwlc.abstract: Coefficient of length and width crossterm dependence for DLC for capacitance models.

wl.abstract: Coefficient of length dependence for WINT.

ww.abstract: Coefficient of width dependence for WINT.

wwl.abstract: Coefficient of length and width cross term dependence for WINT.

wln.abstract: Power of length dependence for WINT.

wwn.abstract: Power of width dependence for WINT.

wlc.abstract: Coefficient of length dependence for DWC for capacitance models.

wwc.abstract: Coefficient of width dependence for DWC for capacitance models.

wwlc.abstract: Coefficient of length and width crossterm dependence for DWC for capacitance models.

dwg.abstract: Coefficient of gate bias dependence of Weff. Default = 0.0m/V.

dwb.abstract: Coefficient of body bias dependence of Weff bias dependence. Default = 0.0m/(V^1/2).

tnom.abstract: Nominal temperature at which model parameters are extracted.

bg0sub.abstract: Band gap of the substrate at 0 Kelvin for MTRLMOD = 1. Default = 1.16 in [eV].

tbgasub.abstract: Temperature dependence parameter of the band gap of the substrate for MTRLMOD =1. Default = 7.02 ¡Á 10^-4 in [eV/Kelvin].

tbgbsub.abstract: Temperature dependence parameter of the band gap of the substrate for MTRLMOD =1. Default = 1108.0 in [Kelvin].

ni0sub.abstract: Intrinsic carrier concentration of the substrate at 300.15 degree Kelvin for MTRLMOD = 1. Default = 1.45 ¡Á 10^10 in [cm^-3 ].
ni0sub.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if it is not positive.

nsd.abstract: Doping concentrations of the source and drain diffusion regions. Default = 1.0 ¡Á 10^20 in [cm^-3 ].

ndep.notice: If its binned value is not positive, a fatal error message will be issued.

ngate.abstract: The doping concentration of poly-silicon gate.
ngate.notice: If its binned value is less than zero, a fatal error message will be issued.

nsub.notice: If its binned value is not positive, a fatal error message will be issued.

vth0.abstract: Long-channel zero body bias threshold voltage. Default = Computed if not given, in unit of [V].

vfb.abstract: Flat-band voltage. Default = Computed if not given, in unit of [V].

dvt0.notice: If its binned value is less than 0, a warning message will be issued.

dvt1.notice: If its binned value is less than 0, a fatal error message will be issued.

dvt2.abstract: Body-bias coefficient of the characteristic length of the V th roll-off model.Default = -0.032 in [V^-1 ].

k1.abstract: First-order body bias coefficient of the Vth model. Default = 0.53 in [V^-1/2 ].
k1.notice: If it is not given but K2 is, it will be set to 0.53. If neither is given, it will be computed.

k2.abstract: Second-order body bias coefficient of the Vth model for non-uniform vertical doping. Default = -0.0186.
k2.notice: If it is not given but K1 is, it will be set to -0.0186. If neither is given, it will be computed.

xt.abstract: The depth of the delta doping. Default = 1.55 ¡Á 10^-7 in [m].

vbm.abstract: The maximum body voltage applicable to a given process technology. Default = -3.0 in [V].

gamma1.abstract: First-order body bias coefficient of the Vth model. Default = Computed from NDEP if not specified, in unit of [V^-1/2 ]. (near the surface)

gamma2.abstract: First-order body bias coefficient of the Vth model. Default = Computed from NSUB if not specified, in unit of [V^-1/2 ]. (in the bulk)

vbx.abstract: The body voltage at which the depletion width is equal to XT. Default = Computed if not specified, in unit of [V].

k3.abstract: Narrow-width effect for the Vth model. Default = 80.0.

k3b.abstract: Narrow-width effect for the Vth model (Body effect). Default = 0.0 in [V^-1 ].

phin.abstract: Surface potential offset parameter owing to non-uniform vertical doping. Default = 0.0 in [V].
phin.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if it produces a negative surface potential.

w0.abstract: Narrow-width effect model parameter for the widest device for the V th model. Default = 2.5 ¡Á 10^-6 in [m].
w0.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if its binned value has the opposite value Weff because of divide-by-zero error.

dvt0w.abstract: Narrow-width and short-channel coefficient parameter for the Vth model. Default = 0.0.

dvt1w.abstract: Narrow-width and short-channel dependence parameter for the Vth model. Default = 5.3 ¡Á 10^-6.
dvt1w.notice: If its binned value is less than 0, a fatal error message will be issued.

dvt2w.abstract: Body-bias coefficient parameter of the width-dependence characteristic length for the Vth model. Default = -0.032 in [V^-1 ].

dsub.abstract: Length-dependence parameter for the Vth DIBL effects. Default = DROUT = 0.56.
dsub.notice: If its binned value is negative, a fatal error message will be issued.

eta0.abstract: Vds-dependence coefficient for the Vth DIBL model. Default = 0.08
eta0.notice: If its binned value is negative, a warning message will be issued.

etab.abstract: Body-bias coefficient for the V th DIBL model. Default = -0.07.
etab.notice: If its binned value is negative, a warning message will be issued.

lpe0.abstract: Vth roll-up parameter owing to pocket implants. It models the increase in the equivalent channel doping. Default = 1.74 ¡Á 10^-7 in [m].
lpe0.notice: If its binned value is less than Leff , a fatal error message will be issued.

lpeb.abstract: Vth roll-up parameter owing to pocket implants. It models the increase in the body-bias effect because of the increase in the equivalent channel doping. Default = 0.0 in [m].
lpeb.notice: If its binned value is less than Leff , a fatal error message will be issued.

dvtp0.abstract: Length-dependence of DITS (drain-induced threshold shifts) of pocket-implanted devices. Default = 0.0 in [m].
dvtp0.notice: If its binned value is not positive, no DITS will be modeled.

dvtp1.abstract: Drain bias dependence of DITS (drain-induced threshold shifts) of pocket-implanted devices. Default = 0.0 in [V^-1 ].

xj.abstract: Source and drain junction depth. Default = 1.5 ¡Á 10^-7 in [m].
xj.notice: If its binned value is negative, a fatal error message will be issued.

kt1.abstract: Temperature-dependence coefficient parameter of the threshold voltage model. Default = -0.11 in [V].

kt1l.abstract: Channel-length dependence parameter of the threshold voltage temperature-dependence model. Default = 0.0 in [V  m].

kt2.abstract: Body bias coefficient parameter for the threshold voltage temperature-dependence model. Default = 0.022.

a0.abstract: Length-dependence of the Abulk model. Default = 1.0.

b0.abstract: The first width-dependence of the Abulk model. Default = 0.0 in [m].

b1.abstract: The second width-dependence of the Abulk model. Default = 0.0 in [m].
b1.notice: If the sum its binned value and Weff becomes zero, a fatal error message will be issued.

keta.abstract: Body-bias coefficient of the Abulk model. Default = -0.047 in [V^-1 ].

ags.abstract: Gate bias (Vgs) dependence of the Abulk model. Default = 0.0 in [V^-1 ].

rdsw.abstract: Zero-bias source and drain LDD resistance component per unit width for RDSMOD = 0. Default = 200.0 in [ohm ¡Á (um)^WR ].
rdsw.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value is less than zero. It will then be reset to zero.

wr.abstract: The power of the width dependence of source and drain LDD resistances. Default = 1.0.

rdswmin.abstract: Source and drain LDD resistance component per unit width at zero body bias and high gate voltages for RDSMOD = 0. Default = 0.0 in [ohm ¡Á (um)^WR ].
rdswmin.notice: A warning message will be issued if it is less than zero. It will then be reset to zero.

prwg.abstract: Gate bias dependence parameter of the LDD source and drain resistances. Default = 1.0 in [V^-1 ].
prwg.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value is less than zero. It will then be reset to zero.

prwb.abstract: Body bias dependence parameter of the LDD source and drain resistances. Default = 0.0 in [V^-0.5 ].

rdw.abstract: Zero-bias drain LDD resistance component per unit width for RDSMOD = 1. Default = 100.0 in [ohm ¡Á (um)^WR ].
rdw.notice: A warning message will be issued if its temperature de-rated value at Temp is negative. Its temperature de-rated value will then be reset to zero.

rdwmin.abstract: Drain LDD resistance component per unit width at zero body bias and high gate voltages for RDSMOD = 1. Default = 0.0 in [ohm ¡Á (um)^WR ].
rdwmin.notice: A warning message will be issued if its temperature de-rated value at Temp is negative. Its temperature de-rated value will then be reset to zero.

rsw.abstract: Zero-bias source LDD resistance component per unit width for RDSMOD = 1. Default = 100.0 in [ohm ¡Á (um)^WR ].
rsw.notice: A warning message will be issued if its temperature de-rated value at Temp is negative. Its temperature de-rated value will then be reset to zero.

rswmin.abstract: Source LDD resistance component per unit width at zero body bias and high gate voltages for RDSMOD = 1. Default = 0.0 in [ohm ¡Á (um)^WR ].
rswmin.notice: A warning message will be issued if its temperature de-rated value at Temp is negative. Its temperature de-rated value will then be reset to zero.

prt.abstract: Temperature dependence coefficient of the source and drain LDD resistances. Default = 0.0 in [ohm ¡Á (um)^WR ] for TEMPMOD = 0 and 0.0 in [1/Kelvin] for other TEMPMOD settings (= 1, 2 or 3).

ados.abstract: Inversion charge thickness parameter to account the density of states, used in both the DC channel current and the CAPMOD = 2 charge and capacitance models. Default = 1.0.

bdos.abstract: Inversion charge thickness power parameter to account the density of states, used in both the DC channel current and the CAPMOD = 2 charge and capacitance models.Default = 1.0.

phig.abstract: Work function of (metal) gates. Default = 4.05 in [V].

easub.abstract: Electron affinity of substrates. Default = 4.05 in [V].
easub.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if it is negative.

u0.abstract: Low-field mobility. Default = 0.067 for NMOS and 0.025 for PMOS in [m^2 /(V ¡Á s)].
u0.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if its temperature de-rated value at Temp is not positive.

up.abstract: Coefficient of the channel-length dependence of the low-field mobility U0. Default = 0.0.

lp.abstract: Exponent of the channel-length dependence of the low-field mobility U0. Default = 1.0 ¡Á 10^-8 in [m].

ua.abstract: First-order gate bias (Vgs) dependence for the effective mobility model. Default = 1.0 ¡Á 10^-15 for MOBMOD = 2 and 1.0 ¡Á 10^-9 for all others in [m/V].

ub.abstract: Secon-order gate bias(Vgs) dependence for the effective mobility model. Default = 1.0 ¡Á 10^-19 in [(m/V)^2 ].

uc.abstract: Body bias dependence for the effective mobility model. Default = -0.0465 for MOBMOD = 1 and -0.0465 ¡Á 10^-9 for all others in [m/V^2 for MOBMOD = 0; V^-1 for MOBMOD = 1; and m^EU/V^(EU+1) for MOBMOD = 2 and 3].

ud.abstract: Coulomb scattering dependence parameter for the effective mobility model. Default = 0.0 in [m^-2 for MOBMOD = 0, 1, and 2; dimensionless for MOBMOD = 3].

eu.abstract: Power of the field dependence for the Coulomb scattering of the effective mobility model MOBMOD = 2 and 3. Default = 1.67 for NMOS and 1.0 for PMOS.
eu.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value is negative. It will be reset to 0.0.

ucs.abstract: Power of the gate bias dependence for the Coulomb scattering of the effective mobility model MOBMOD = 3. Default = 1.67 for NMOS and 1.0 for PMOS.
ucs.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value is negative. It will be reset to 0.0.

ute.abstract: Power of low-field mobility U0  temperature dependence. Default = -1.5.

ucste.abstract: Power of temperature dependence of UCS. Default = -4.775 ¡Á 10^-3 .

ua1.abstract: Temperature dependence coefficient of the parameter UA. Default = 1.0 ¡Á 10^-9 in [The same unit as UA for TEMPMOD = 0; 1/Kelvin for TEMPMOD = 1 and 2; and dimensionless for TEMPMOD = 3].

ub1.abstract: Temperature dependence coefficient of UB. Default = -1.0 ¡Á 10^-18 in [The same unit as UB for TEMPMOD = 0; 1/Kelvin for TEMPMOD = 1 and 2; and dimensionless for TEMPMOD = 3].

uc1.abstract: Temperature dependence coefficient of UC.Default = -0.056 for MOBMOD = 1 and -0.056 ¡Á 10^-9 for all others in [The same unit as UC for TEMPMOD = 0; 1/Kelvin for TEMPMOD = 1 and 2; and dimensionless for TEMPMOD = 3].

ud1.abstract: Temperature dependence coefficient of the parameter UD. Default = 0.0 in [The same unit as UD for TEMPMOD = 0; 1/Kelvin for TEMPMOD = 1 and 2; and dimensionless for TEMPMOD = 3].

saref.abstract: Reference spacing in the channel length direction between one edge of the OD and one edge of the gate. Default = 1.0 ¡Á 10^-6 in [m].
saref.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if it is not positive when the LOD model is turned on.

sbref.abstract: Reference spacing in the channel length direction between the other edge of the OD and the other edge of the gate. Default = 1.0 ¡Á 10^-6 in [m].
sbref.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if it is not positive when the LOD model is turned on.

ku0.abstract: Mobility enhancement/reduction coefficient because of LOD. Default = 0.0 in [m].

tku0.abstract: Temperature dependence for KU0 of the LOD model. Default = 0.0 in [1/Kelvin].

lku0.abstract: Length dependence of KU0. Default = 0.0 in [m^LLODKU0 ].

wku0.abstract: Width dependence of KU0. Default = 0.0 in [m^WLODKU0 ].

pku0.abstract: Width and length cross-term dependence parameter of KU0. Default = 0.0 in [m^(LLODKU0 + WLODKU0) ].

llodku0.abstract: The power of the length dependence of KU0. Default = 0.0.

wlodku0.abstract: The power of the width dependence of KU0. Default = 0.0.

wlod.abstract: Channel width offset parameter for LOD. Default = 0.0 in [m].

kvsat.abstract: Saturation velocity enhancement/reduction coefficient because of LOD. Default = 0.0.
kvsat.notice: A warning message will be issued and it will be reset to -1.0 if less than -1.0. A warning message will be issued and it will be reset to 1.0 if greater than 1.0.

kvth0.abstract: Threshold voltage increase/decrease parameter because of LOD. Default = 0.0 in [V ¡Á m].

lkvth0.abstract: Length dependence of KVTH0. Default = 0.0 in [m^LLODVTH ].

wkvth0.abstract: Width dependence of KVTH0. Default = 0.0 in [m^WLODVTH ].

pkvth0.abstract: Width and length cross-term dependence of KVTH0. Default = 0.0 in [m^(LLODVTH + WLODVTH) ].

llodvth.abstract: The power of the length dependence of KVTH0. Default = 0.0.

wlodvth.abstract: The power of the width dependence of KVTH0. Default = 0.0.

stk2.abstract: K2 increase/decrease parameter because of LOD. Default = 0.0 in [m].

lodk2.abstract: The power of the geometry dependence of STK2 because of LOD. Default = 1.0.
lodk2.notice: A warning message will be issues when it is not positive and when the LOD model  evaluation is turned on.

steta0.abstract: ETA0 increase/decrease parameter because of LOD. Default = 0.0 in [m].

lodeta0.abstract: The power of the geometry dependence of STETA0 because of LOD. Default = 1.0.
lodeta0.notice: A warning message will be issues when it is not positive and when the LOD model evaluation is turned on.

scref.abstract: The reference value of SC of the WPE model. Default = 1 ¡Á 10^-6 in [m].
scref.notice: A warning message will be issued if it is less than or equal to zero when the WPE model is turned. It is then reset to 1.0 ¡Á 10^-6 m.

ku0we.abstract: Coefficient for the low-field mobility U0 because of WPE. Default = 0.0.

kvth0we.abstract: Coefficient for VTH0 because of WPE. Default = 0.0 in [V].

k2we.abstract: Coefficient for K2 because of WPE. Default = 0.0.

web.abstract: Coefficient of SCB because of WPE.

wec.abstract: Coefficient of SCC because of WPE.

voff.abstract: Offset voltage of the effective gate drive.Default = -0.08 in [V].

voffl.abstract: Length dependence for VOFF. Default = 0.0 in [V ¡Á m].

tvoff.abstract: Temperature dependence for VOFF. Default = 0.0 in [1/Kelvin].

minv.abstract: Parameter for the DC channel current in the moderate inversion region. Default = 0.0.

nfactor.abstract: Coefficient of the depletion capacitance dependence of the subthreshold slope parameter n. Default = 1.0.
nfactor.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value becomes negative.

cdsc.abstract: Drain-source and the channel coupling capacitance for the subthreshold slope parameter n. Default = 2.4 ¡Á 10^-4 in [Farad/m^2].
cdsc.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value becomes negative.

cdscd.abstract: Drain-bias dependence coefficient of CDSC. Default = 0.0 in [Farad/m^2/V].
cdscd.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value becomes negative.

cdscb.abstract: Body-bias dependence coefficient of CDSC. Default = 0.0 in [Farad/m^2/V].

cit.abstract: Unit-area capacitance owing to the interface  states for the subthreshold slope parameter n. Default = 0.0 in [Farad/m^2].

vsat.abstract: Channel carrier saturation velocity extracted at TNOM. Default = 8.0 ¡Á 10^4 in [m/s].
vsat.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if its value after temperature de-rating is not positive; a warning message will be issued if its value after temperature de-rating is less than 1 ¡Á 10^3 .

at.abstract: Temperature-dependence parameter for the saturation velocity VSAT. Default = 3.3 ¡Á 10^4 in [m/s] for TEMPMOD = 0 and 3.3 ¡Á 10^4 in [1/Kelvin] for other TEMPMOD  settings (i.e., 1, 2, and 3).

a1.abstract: PMOS non-saturation effect parameter. Default = 0.0 in [V^-1].
a1.notice: Reset to zero if A2 is greater than 1.0.

a2.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value is less than 0.1 and will be reset to 0.1. A warning message will be issued if its binned value is greater than 1.0 and it will be reset to 1.0.

delta.abstract: Parameter of the effective source-drain voltage Vdseff used in the DC current model. It models how rapid carrier velocity saturates when Vds near the saturation voltage Vdsat . Default = 0.01.
delta.notice: A fatal errormessage will be issued if its binned value is negative.

pclm.abstract: Channel-length modulation effects on the channel output resistance degradation. Default = 1.3.
pclm.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if its binned value is not positive.

pvag.abstract: Gate bias dependence parameter to model the channel-length modulation effects on the channel output resistance degradation. Default = 0.0.

pdiblcb.abstract: Body bias dependence to model the DIBL effects on the channel output resistance degradation. Default = 0.0 in [V^-1].

pdiblc1.abstract: Channel-length dependence to model the DIBL effects on the channel output resistance degradation. Default = 0.39.
pdiblc1.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value is less than zero.

pdiblc2.abstract: Channel-length dependence to model the DIBL effects on the channel output resistance degradation. Default = 0.0086.
pdiblc2.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value is less than zero.

drout.abstract: Channel-length dependence coefficient to model the DIBL effects on the channel output resistance degradation. Default = 0.56.
drout.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if its binned value is less than zero.

fprout.abstract: Coefficient for the channel output resistance degradation due to pocket implants. Default = 0.0 in [V/m^-1/2 ].
fprout.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if its binned value is negative.

pdits.abstract: Rout degradation coefficient due to drain-induced threshold voltage shifts caused by pocket implants. Default = 0.0 in [V^-1].
pdits.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if its binned value is negative.

pditsl.abstract: Length-dependence for drain-induced threshold voltage shifts caused by pocket implants. Default = 0.0 in [m^-1].
pditsl.notice: A fatal error message will be issued if its value is negative.

pditsd.abstract: Drain bias dependence for drain-induced threshold voltage shifts caused by pocket implants. Default = 0.0 in [V^-1 ].

pscbe1.abstract: Drain bias dependence parameter for the substrate current induced body effect. Default = 4.24 ¡Á 10^8 in [V/m].

pscbe2.abstract: Length-dependence parameter for the substrate current induced body effect. Default = 1.0 ¡Á 10^-5 in [m/V].
pscbe2.notice: A warning message will be issued if its binned value is not positive.

lambda.abstract: Parameter to model the velocity overshoot effect on the channel critical electric field Esat . Default = 0.0 in [m^3 /(V ¡Á s)].
lambda.notice: Velocity overshoot model evaluation will be turned on if this parameter if given and greater than zero. A warning message will also be issued if its value is greater than 1 ¡Á 10^-9 (too large!)

vtl.abstract: Electron and hole thermal injection speed at source of the source-end velocity limit model. Default = 2.0 ¡Á 10^5 in [m/s].
vtl.notice: A warning message will be issued when its binned value is less than 6 ¡Á 10^4 (too small), if it is given and its binned value is greater than zero.

xn.abstract: Channel-length dependence coefficient parameter for the backward scattering of the source-end velocity limit model. Default = 3.0.
xn.notice: A warning message will be issued when its binned value is less than 3 (too small), if VTL is given and the binned value of VTL is greater than zero. It will then be reset to 3.

lc.abstract: Critical channel length for the backward scattering of the source-end velocity limit model. Default = 5.0 ¡Á 10^-9 in [m].
lc.notice: A warning message will be issued when its value is less than 0 (too small), if VTL is given and the binned value of VTL is greater than zero. It will then be reset to zero.

igcmod.abstract: Gate-to-channel tunneling current model selector. Default = 0. Optional values are 1 (long-channel zero-bias VTH0 to be used in the gate-and-channel tunneling current model computation) and 2 (the full-equation Vth model to be used in the gate-and-channel tunneling current model computation).
igcmod.notice: IGCMOD = 1 and 2  turns on Igs , Igd , Igcs and Igcd.

nf.notice: Reset to 1 if  less than 1 with a warning to be issued.

aigbacc.abstract: Parameter for Igb in accumulation. Default = 9.49e-4 in [(Fs^2/g)^0.5 m^-1].

bigbacc.abstract: Parameter for Igb in accumulation. Default = 1.71e-3 in [(Fs^2/g)^0.5 (mV)^-1].

cigbacc.abstract: Parameter for Igb in accumulation. Default = 0.075 in [V^-1].

nigbacc.abstract: Parameter for Igb in accumulation. Default = 1.0.
nigbacc.notice: Fatal errors to be issued if  its binned value is less than 0.

aigbinv.abstract: Parameter for Igb in inversion. Default = 1.11e-2 in [(Fs^2/g)^0.5 m^-1].

bigbinv.abstract: Parameter for Igb in inversion. Default =  9.49e-4 in [(Fs^2/g)^0.5 (mV)^-1].

cigbinv.abstract: Parameter for Igb in inversion. Default = 0.006 in [V^-1].

eigbinv.abstract: Parameter for Igb in inversion. Default = 1.1 in [V].

nigbinv.abstract: Parameter for Igb in inversion. Default = 3.0.
nigbinv.notice: Fatal errors to be issued if  its binned value is less than 0.

aigc.abstract: Parameter for the Igcs and Igcd model. Default = 1.36e-2 for NMOS; 9.8e-3 for PMOS in [(Fs^2/g)^0.5 m^-1].

bigc.abstract: Parameter for the Igcs and Igcd model. Default = 1.71e-3 for NMOS; 7.59e-4 for PMOS in [(Fs^2/g)^0.5 (mV)^-1].

cigc.abstract: Parameter for the Igcs and Igcd model. Default = 0.075 for NMOS; 0.03 for PMOS  in [V^-1].

aigsd.abstract: Parameter for the Igs and Igd model. Default = 1.36e-2 for NMOS; 9.8e-3 for PMOS in [(Fs^2/g)^0.5 m^-1].

bigsd.abstract: Parameter for the Igs and Igd model. Default = 1.71e-3 for NMOS; 7.59e-4 for PMOS in [(Fs^2/g)^0.5 (mV)^-1].

cigsd.abstract: Parameter for the Igs and Igd model. Default = 0.075 for NMOS; 0.03 for PMOS  in [V^-1].

vfbsdoff.abstract: offset flat-band voltage for the source and drain diffusion regions. Default = 0.0 in [V].

tvfbsdoff.abstract: Temperature coefficient of VFBSDOFF. Default = 0.0 in [K^-1].

dlcig.abstract: Source and drain overlap length for the Igs and Igd models. Default = LINT in [meter].

nigc.abstract: Parameter for the Igs, Igd, Igcs, and Igcd models. Default = 1.0.
nigc.notice: Fatal errors to be issued if  its binned value is less than 0.

poxedge.abstract: Factor for the gate oxide thickness in source/drain overlap regions. Default = 1.0.
poxedge.notice: Fatal errors to be issued if  its binned value is less than 0.

pigcd.abstract: Gate-and-channel tunneling current Igc partitioning parameter. Default = 1.0.
pigcd.notice: Fatal errors to be issued if  its binned value is less than 0.

ntox.abstract: Exponent for the gate oxide ratio. Default = 1.0.

alpha0.abstract: First parameter of impact ionization current. Default = 0.0 in [meter/V].

alpha1.abstract: Channel length scaling parameter of impact ionization current. Default = 0.0 in [V^-1].

beta0.abstract: First Vds dependent parameter of impact ionization current. Default = 0.0 in [V].

agidl.abstract: Pre-exponential coefficient for GIDL. Default = 0.0 in [mho].
agidl.notice: If not positive, IGIDL will not be computed.

agisl.abstract: Pre-exponential coefficient for GISL. Default = AGIDL if AGIDL is given; otherwise is set to 0.0 in [mho].
agisl.notice: If not positive, IGISL will not be computed.

bgidl.abstract: Exponential coefficient for GIDL. Default = 2.3 ¡Á 10^9 in [V/m].
bgidl.notice: If not positive, IGIDL will not be computed.

bgisl.abstract: Exponential coefficient for GISL. Default = BGIDL if BGIDL is given; otherwise it is set to 2.3 ¡Á 10^9 in [V/m].
bgisl.notice: If not positive, IGISL will not be computed.

cgidl.abstract: Paramter for body-bias effect on GIDL. Default = 0.5 in [V^3].
cgidl.notice: If not positive, IGIDL will not be computed.

cgisl.abstract: Paramter for body-bias effect on GISL. Default = CGISL if CGISL is given; otherwise it is set to 0.5 in [V^3].
cgisl.notice: If not positive, IGISL will not be computed.

egidl.abstract: Fitting parameter for band bending for GIDL. Default = 0.8 in [V].

egisl.abstract: Fitting parameter for band bending for GISL. Default = EGISL if EGISL is given; otherwise, it is set to 0.8 in [V].

capmod.abstract: Charge and capacitance model selector. Default = 2. The other optional values are 0 and 1.

xpart.abstract: Channel charge partitioning selector. Default = 0.0 (the 40/60 partition). The other optional values are 0.5 (50/50) and 1.0 (0/100).
xpart.notice: If it is set less than 0 (a very rare or mistaken setting), no intrinsic charge and capacitance model will be evaluated.

cvchargemod.abstract: Vgsteff model selector for CAPMOD = 1 and 2. Default = 0. The other optional value is a non-zero value, such as 1.
cvchargemod.notice: The default uses a simple Vgsteff .

acde.abstract: Exponential coefficient for charge thickness in CAPMOD=2 for accumulation and depletion regions. Default = 1.0.
acde.notice: Warning messages to be issued if its binned value is either less than 0.1 or great than 1.6.

ados.abstract: Inversion charge thickness parameter to account for the density of states, used in both the DC channel current and the CAPMOD = 2. Default = 1.0.

bdos.abstract: Inversion charge thickness power parameter to account for the density of states, used in both the DC channel current and the CAPMOD = 2. Default = 1.0.

noff.abstract: CV parameter in Vgsteff,CV for weak to strong inversion. Default = 1.0.

voffcv.abstract: Offset voltage parameter to shift CV curves with respect to the gate voltage for CAPMOD = 1 and 2. Default = 0.0.

voffcvl.abstract: Length-dependence parameter for the offset voltage VOFFCV. Default = 0.0.

vfbcv.abstract: Flat-band voltage parameter (for CAPMOD=0 only). Default = -1.0[V]

minvcv.abstract: Parameter to adjust the CV curvature in the moderate inversion region of CAPMOD = 1 and 2. It is activated if CVCHARGEMOD is not zero. Default = 0.0.

moin.abstract: Coefficient for the gate-bias dependent surface potential in CAPMOD = 2. It is used for more accurate modeling of the moderate inversion region. Default = 15.0.
moin.notice: If its binned value is less than 5 or greater than 25, a warning message will be issued.

clc.abstract: Length-dependence coefficient parameter of the bulk charge effect parameter Abulk_CV. Default = 0.1 ¡Á 10^-6 in [m].
clc.notice: If the binned value is negative, a fatal message will be issued.

cle.abstract: Length-dependence coefficient parameter of the bulk charge effect parameter Abulk_CV. Default = 0.6.

cf.abstract: Outer fringing capacitance per unit width. Default = Computed if not given in [Farad per meter].

cgdo.abstract: Non LDD region drain-gate overlap capacitance per unit channel width. Default: Refer to the text for various possible scenarios.

cgso.abstract: Non LDD region source-gate overlap capacitance per unit channel width. Default: Refer to the text for various possible scenarios.

cgbo.abstract: Gate-bulk overlap capacitance per unit channel length. Default: Refer to the text for various possible scenarios.

cgdl.abstract: Overlap capacitance between gate and lightly-doped drain region. Default = 0.0 in [Farad/m].

cgsl.abstract: Overlap capacitance between gate and lightly-doped source region. Default = 0.0 in [Farad/m].

ckappas.abstract: Coefficient of bias-dependent overlap capacitance for the source side. Default = 0.6 in [V].
ckappas.notice: If its binned value is less than 0.02, a warning message will be issued and it is reset to 0.02.

ckappad.abstract: Coefficient of bias-dependent overlap capacitance for the drain side. Default = CKAPPAS in [V].
ckappad.notice: If its binned value is less than 0.02, a warning message will be issued and it is reset to 0.02.

rgatemod.abstract: Gate resistance model selector. Default = 0; No gate resistance is to be generated. Other optional values are 1, 2, or 3.

rbodymod.abstract: Body-resistance network model selector. Default = 0;  No network is to be generated. Other optional values are 1 or 2.

trnqsmod.abstract: Charge-deficit transient NQS model selector. Default = 0; Charge-deficit transient NQS model is turned off. Other optional value is 1 (turned on).
trnqsmod.notice: When TRNQSMOD is set to 1, do not make RGATEMOD equal to 2 or 3; vice versa.

acnqsmod.abstract: Charge-deficit AC NQS model selector. Default = 0; Charge-deficit AC NQS model is turned off. Other optional value is 1 (turned on).
acnqsmod.notice: When ACNQSMOD is set to 1, do not make RGATEMOD equal to 2 or 3; vice versa.

rshg.notice: If RSHG <= 0, a warning will be issued.

ngcon.abstract: Poly-silicon gate contact type selector. Default = 1; Gate contact made only on one side of the gate. Other optional value is 2 (two-sided contact).
ngcon.notice: If NGCON is less than 1, a fatal error will be issued.

xgw.abstract: Distance from the gate contact to the device edge. Default = 0.0 [m].

xgl.abstract: The offset between the actual poly-silicon gate (not the channel) length and the designed length of the poly-silicon gate. Default = 0.0 [m].
xgl.notice: If (Ldrawn + XL) < XGL, a fatal error will be issued.

xrcrg1.abstract: The intrinsic-input gate resistance R_g,ii fitting parameter for both drift and diffusion components. Default = 12.0.
xrcrg1.notice: If XRCRG1 < 0, a warning will be given.

xrcrg2.abstract: The intrinsic-input gate resistance R_g,ii fitting parameter for the diffusion component only when Vgs is close to or less than Vth. Default = 1.0.

gbmin.abstract: The minimum conductance set for each body-resistance network branch to prevent too high resistances that would otherwise make convergence difficult. Default = 10^-12 [mho].
gbmin.notice: If it is less than 10^-20 mho, a warning will be given.

rbpd.abstract: The body resistance component connecting sbNodePrime and dbNode. Default = 50.0 [ohm].

rbps.abstract: The body resistance component connecting sbNodePrime and sbNode. Default = 50.0 [ohm].

rbpb.abstract: The body resistance component connecting sbNodePrime and bNode. Default = 50.0 [ohm].

rbdb.abstract: The body resistance component connecting dbNode and bNode. Default = 50.0 [ohm].

rbsb.abstract: The body resistance component connecting sbNode and bNode. Default = 50.0 [ohm].

rbpd0.notice: Used for 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbpdl.abstract: Length Scaling parameter for RBPD. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbpdl.notice: Used for 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbpdw.abstract: Width Scaling parameter for RBPD. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbpdw.notice: Used for 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbpdnf.abstract: Number of fingers Scaling parameter for RBPD. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbpdnf.notice: Used for 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbps0.notice: Used for 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbpsl.abstract: Length Scaling parameter for RBPS. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbpsl.notice: Used for 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbpsw.abstract: Width Scaling parameter for RBPS. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbpsw.notice: Used for 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbpsnf.abstract: Number of fingers Scaling parameter for RBPS. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbpsnf.notice: Used for 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbpbx0.notice: Used for 1-R, 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbpbxl.notice: Used for 1-R, 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 3 only.

rbpbxw.abstract: Width Scaling parameter for RBPBX. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbpbxw.notice: Used for 1-R, 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 4 only.

rbpbxnf.abstract: Number of fingers Scaling parameter for RBPBX. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbpbxnf.notice: Used for 1-R, 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 5 only.

rbpby0.notice: Used for 1-R, 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 6 only.

rbpbyl.notice: Used for 1-R, 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 7 only.

rbpbyw.abstract: Width Scaling parameter for RBPBY. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbpbyw.notice: Used for 1-R, 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 8 only.

rbpbynf.abstract: Number of fingers Scaling parameter for RBPBY. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbpbynf.notice: Used for 1-R, 3-R and 5-R options of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbdbx0.notice: Used for the 5-R option of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbdby0.notice: Used for the 5-R option of RBODYMOD = 2 only.

rbsbx0.notice: Used for the 5-R option of RBODYMOD = 3 only.

rbsby0.notice: Used for the 5-R option of RBODYMOD = 4 only.

rbsdbxl.abstract: Length Scaling parameter for RBSBX and RBDBX. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbsdbxl.notice: Used for the 5-R option of RBODYMOD = 5 only.

rbsdbxw.abstract: Width Scaling parameter for RBSBX and RBDBX. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbsdbxw.notice: Used for the 5-R option of RBODYMOD = 6 only.

rbsdbxnf.abstract: Number of fingers Scaling parameter for RBSBX and RBDBX. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbsdbxnf.notice: Used for the 5-R option of RBODYMOD = 7 only.

rbsdbyl.abstract: Length Scaling parameter for RBSBY and RBDBY. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbsdbyl.notice: Used for the 5-R option of RBODYMOD = 8 only.

rbsdbyw.abstract: Width Scaling parameter for RBSBY and RBDBY. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbsdbyw.notice: Used for the 5-R option of RBODYMOD = 9 only.

rbsdbynf.abstract: Number of fingers Scaling parameter for RBSBY and RBDBY. Default = 0.0 [ohm].
rbsdbynf.notice: Used for the 5-R option of RBODYMOD = 10 only.

fnoimod.abstract: Flicker noise model selector. Default = 1. The other optional value is 0.

kf.abstract: The FNOIMOD = 0 flicker noise coefficient. Default = 1.0 in [A^(2-AF) ¡Á s^(1-EF) ¡Á Farad].

af.abstract: The FNOIMOD = 0 flicker noise channel current exponent. Default = 1.0.

noia.abstract: The FNOIMOD = 1 flicker noise equivalent trap density parameter A. Default = NMOS: 6.25 ¡Á 10^41 (eV )^-1 ¡Á s^(1-EF) ¡Á m^-3 ; PMOS: 6.188 ¡Á 10^40 (eV)^-1 ¡Á s^( 1-EF) ¡Á m^-3.

noib.abstract: The FNOIMOD = 1 flicker noise equivalent trap density parameter B. Default = NMOS: 3.125 ¡Á 10^26 (eV )^-1 ¡Á s^(1-EF) ¡Á m^-1 ; PMOS: 1.5 ¡Á 10^25 (eV)^-1 ¡Á s^( 1-EF) ¡Á m^-1.

noic.abstract: The FNOIMOD = 1 flicker noise equivalent trap density parameter C. Default = 8.75 ¡Á 10^9 in [(eV)^-1 ¡Á s^(1-EF) ¡Á m].

em.abstract: Maximum channel electric field strength of the FNOIMOD = 1 flicker noise model. Default = 4.1 ¡Á 10^7 in [V ¡Á m^-1 ].

lintnoi.abstract: The gate-to-source/drain overlap length for the FNOIMOD = 1 flicker noise model. Default = 0.0 in [m].
lintnoi.notice: Fatal error if it makes the effective channel  length negative for noise modeling and simulation.

ntnoi.abstract: Noise factor for short-channel devices for TNOIMOD=0 only. Default = 1.0.
ntnoi.notice: If negative, a warning will be issued and its value will be reset to 0.

rnoia.abstract: Noise partitioning coefficient for the TNOIMOD = 1 channel thermal noise model. Default = 0.5164.
rnoia.notice: If negative, a warning will be issued and its value will be reset to 0.

rnoib.abstract: Transconductance amplification coefficient for the TNOIMOD = 1 channel thermal noise model. Default = 0.577.
rnoib.notice: If negative, a warning will be issued and its value will be reset to 0.

tnoia.abstract: Bias and length dependence parameter for the TNOIMOD = 1 thermal noise model partitioning. Default = 1.5.
tnoia.notice: If negative, a warning will be issued and its value will be reset to 0.

tnoib.abstract: Bias and length dependence parameter for the noise transconductance amplification of the TNOIMOD = 1 thermal noise model. Default = 3.5.
tnoib.notice: If negative, a warning will be issued and its value will be reset to 0.

geomod.abstract: Geometry-dependent parasitics model selector - specifying how the end S/D diffusions are connected. Default = 0; The end diffusions can either be an isolated source or an isolated drain, or both; NF can be an odd or even number. Other optional values are 1 through 10.

permod.abstract: Whether PS/PD (when given) includes the gate-edge perimeter. Default = 1; The BSIM4 source and drain perimeters PS and PD that are explicitly specified in element statements include the gate-edge perimeter components.

rgeomod.abstract: Source/drain diffusion resistance and contact model selector - specifying the end S/D contact type: point, wide or merged, and how S/D parasitics resistance is computed. Default = 0; No source and drain diffusion contact type is considered. Other optional values are 1 through 8.

dmcg.abstract: Distance from S/D contact center to the gate edge. Default = 0.0 [m].

dmcgt.abstract: DMCG of test device structures used in device characterization and model parameter extractions. Default = 0.0 [m].

dmci.abstract: Distance from S/D contact center to the (STI) isolation edge in the channel-length direction. Default = DMCG [m].

dmdg.abstract: Same as DMCG but for merged device only. Default = 0.0 [m].

min.abstract: An integer flag to indicate whether the end diffusions are source or drain when the number of finger (NF) is even. Default = 0; the end diffusions serve as the source terminal.

ps.abstract: The source junction perimeter. It is meant to include the gate-edge perimeter component when PERMOD = 1. The GEOMOD model will be used to compute the total effective source perimeter value when PS is not explicitly specified in element statements. Default = 0.0 [m].
ps.notice: From BSIM4.5.0 onwards, a warning message will be issued if a negative PS is given. The effective source perimeter PSeff will then be set to zero regardless of the setting of PERMOD.

pd.abstract: The drain junction perimeter. It is meant to include the gate-edge perimeter component when PERMOD = 1. The GEOMOD model will be used to compute the total effective drain perimeter value when PD is not explicitly specified in element statements. Default = 0.0 [m].
pd.notice: From BSIM4.5.0 onwards, a warning message will be issued if a negative PD is given. The effective source perimeter PDeff will then be set to zero regardless of the setting of PERMOD.

as.abstract: The source junction bottom area. The GEOMOD model will be used to compute the effective source bottom area value when AS is not explicitly specified in element statements. Default = 0.0 [m^2 ].

ad.abstract: The drain junction bottom area. The GEOMOD model will be used to compute the effective drain bottom area value when AD is not explicitly specified in element statements. Default = 0.0 [m^2 ].

nrs.abstract: Number of squares of the source diffusion region. Default = 1.0 [square].

nrd.abstract: Number of squares of the drain diffusion region. Default = 1.0 [square].

diomod.abstract: Source/drain junction diode IV model selector. Default = 1. Other optional values are 0 and 2.

njs.abstract: Emission coefficients (The non-ideality factor) of junction for source-bulk junctions. Default = 1.0.
njs.notice: A warning to be issued if it is negative.

njd.abstract: Emission coefficients (The non-ideality factor) of junction for drain-bulk junctions. Default = NJS.
njd.notice: A warning to be issued if it is negative.

xjbvs.abstract: Fitting parameter for source-bulk junction diode break-down. In the case of DIOMOD = 0. XJBVS will be reset to 1 if it is negative. XJBVS = 0 means no breakdown will be modeled. In the case of DIOMOD = 2, XJBVS will be reset to 1 if it is not positive. Default = 1.0.

xjbvd.abstract: Fitting parameter for drain-bulk junction diode break-down. In the case of DIOMOD = 0. XJBVD will be reset to 1 if it is negative. XJBVD = 0 means no breakdown will be modeled. In the case of DIOMOD = 2, XJBVD will be reset to 1 if it is not positive. Default = XJBVS.

bvs.abstract: Source-bulk junction diode breakdown voltage. Default = 10.0 in [V].
bvs.notice: If BVS is not positive, it is reset to 10 V.

bvd.abstract: Drain-bulk junction diode breakdown voltage. Default = BVS in [V].
bvd.notice: If BVD is not positive, it is reset to 10 V.

ijthsfwd.abstract: Limiting source junction current at which the source junction current equation is linearized for the forward body bias regime. Default = 0.1 in [A].
ijthsfwd.notice: If IJTHSFWD is not positive, it will be reset to 0.1 A.

ijthdfwd.abstract: Limiting drain junction current at which the drain junction current equation is linearized for the forward body bias regime. Default = IJTHSFWD in [A].
ijthdfwd.notice: If IJTHDFWD is not positive, it will be reset to 0.1 A.

ijthsrev.abstract: Limiting source junction current at which the source junction current equation is linearized for the reverse body bias regime. Default = 0.1 in [A].
ijthsrev.notice: If IJTHSREV is not positive, it will be reset to 0.1 A.

ijthdrev.abstract: Limiting drain junction current at which the drain junction current equation is linearized for the reverse body bias regime.Default = IJTHSREV in [A].
ijthdrev.notice: If IJTHDREV is not positive, it will be reset to 0.1 A.

vtss.abstract: Source junction bottom trap-assisted voltage dependent parameter. Default = 10.0 in [V].
vtss.notice: Fatal error to be issued if it is negative.

vtsd.abstract: Drain junction bottom trap-assisted voltage dependent parameter. Default = VTSS in [V].
vtsd.notice: Fatal error to be issued if it is negative.

vtssws.abstract: Source STI sidewall trap-assisted voltage dependent parameter. Default = 10.0 in [V].
vtssws.notice: Fatal error to be issued if it is negative.

vtsswd.abstract: Drain STI sidewall trap-assisted voltage dependent parameter. Default = VTSSWS in [V].
vtsswd.notice: Fatal error to be issued if it is negative.

vtsswgs.abstract: Source gate-edge sidewall trap-assisted voltage dependent parameter. Default = 10.0 in [V].
vtsswgs.notice: Fatal error to be issued if it is negative.

vtsswgd.abstract: Drain gate-edge sidewall trap-assisted voltage dependent parameter. Default = VTSSWGS in [V].
vtsswgd.notice: Fatal error to be issued if it is negative.

jss.abstract: Saturation current density of the source junction bottom at TNOM. Default = 1.0e-4 in [A/m^2 ].

jsd.abstract: Saturation current density of the drain  junction bottom at TNOM. Default = JSS in [A/m^2 ].

jsws.abstract: Saturation current density of the source STI sidewall junction at TNOM. Default = 0.0 in [A/m].

jswd.abstract: Saturation current density of the drain STI sidewall junction at TNOM. Default = JSWS in [A/m].

jswgs.abstract: Saturation current density of the source gate-edge junction at TNOM. Default = 0.0 in [A/m].

jswgd.abstract: Saturation current density of the drain gate-edge junction at TNOM. Default = JSWGS in [A/m].

xtis.abstract: Exponent of the temperature dependence of the source-bulk junction saturation current density. Default = 3.0.

xtid.abstract: Exponent of the temperature dependence of the drain-bulk junction saturation current density. Default = XTIS.

mjs.abstract: Source-bulk bottom junction grading coefficient for depletion capacitance model. Default = 0.5.
mjs.notice: A warning to be issued if it is greater than or equal to 0.99; reset to 0.99 if it is greater than 0.99 for numerical stability.

mjd.abstract: Drain-bulk bottom junction grading coefficient for depletion capacitance model. Default = MJS.
mjd.notice: A warning to be issued if it is greater than or equal to 0.99; reset to 0.99 if it is greater than 0.99 for numerical stability.

mjsws.abstract: Source-bulk STI sidewall junction grading coefficient for depletion capacitance model. Default = 0.33.
mjsws.notice: A warning to be issued if it is greater than or equal to 0.99; reset to 0.99 if it is greater than 0.99 for numerical stability.

mjswd.abstract: Drain-bulk STI sidewall junction grading coefficient for depletion capacitance model. Default = MJSWS.
mjswd.notice: A warning to be issued if it is greater than or equal to 0.99; reset to 0.99 if it is greater than 0.99 for numerical stability.

mjswgs.abstract: Source-bulk gate-edge junction grading coefficient for depletion capacitance model. Default = MJSWS.
mjswgs.notice: A warning to be issued if it is greater than or equal to 0.99; reset to 0.99 if it is greater than 0.99 for numerical stability.

mjswgd.abstract: Drain-bulk gate-edge junction grading coefficient for depletion capacitance model. Default = MJSWGS.
mjswgd.notice: A warning to be issued if it is greater than or equal to 0.99; reset to 0.99 if it is greater than 0.99 for numerical stability.

jtss.abstract: Trap-assisted tunneling saturation current density of the source-bulk junction bottom at TNOM. Default = 0.0 in [A/m^2 ].

xtss.abstract: Power dependence of JTSS on temperature. Default = 0.02.

jtsd.abstract: Trap-assisted tunneling saturation current density of the drain-bulk junction bottom at TNOM. Default = JTSS in [A/m^2 ].

xtsd.abstract: Power dependence of JTSD on temperature. Default = XTSS.

jtssws.abstract: Source-bulk STI sidewall trap-assisted saturation current density at TNOM. Default = 0.0 in [A/m].

xtssws.abstract: Power dependence of JTSSWS on temperature. Default = 0.02.

jtsswd.abstract: Drain-bulk STI sidewall trap-assisted saturation current density at TNOM. Default = JTSSWS in [A/m].

xtsswd.abstract: Power dependence of JTSSWD on temperature. Default = XTSSWS.

jtsswgs.abstract: Source-bulk gate-edge sidewall trap-assisted saturation current density. Default = 0.0 in [A/m].

xtsswgs.abstract: Power dependence of JTSSWGS on temperature. Default = 0.02.

jtsswgd.abstract: Drain-bulk gate-edge sidewall trap-assisted saturation current density. Default = JTSSWGS in [A/m].

xtsswgd.abstract: Power dependence of JTSSWGD on temperature. Default = XTSSWGS.

njts.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJS_TAT(T) negative.

njtsd.abstract: Non-ideality factor for JTSD. Default = NJTS.
njtsd.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJD_TAT(T) negative.

njtssw.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJSSW_TAT(T) negative.

njtsswd.abstract: Non-ideality factor for JTSSWD. Default = NJTSSW.
njtsswd.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJSSW_TAT(T) negative.

njtsswg.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJSSWG_TAT(T) negative.

njtsswgd.abstract: Non-ideality factor for JTSSWGD. Default = NJTSSWG.
njtsswgd.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJSSWG_TAT(T) negative.

tnjts.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJS_TAT(T) negative.

tnjtsd.abstract: Temperature-dependence coefficient of NJTSD. Default = TNJTS.
tnjtsd.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJD_TAT(T) negative.

tnjtssw.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJSSW_TAT(T) negative.

tnjtsswd.abstract: Temperature-dependence coefficient of NJTSSWD. Default = TNJTSSW.
tnjtsswd.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJSSW_TAT(T) negative.

tnjtsswg.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJSSWG_TAT(T) negative.

tnjtsswgd.abstract: Temperature-dependence coefficient of NJTSSWGD. Default = TNJTSSWG.
tnjtsswgd.notice: A warning to be issued if it makes the temperature-dependent NJSSWG_TAT(T) negative.

cjs.abstract: Source-bulk bottom junction capacitance per unit area at zero bias at TNOM. Default = 5.0 ¡Á 10^4 in [Farad/m^2 ].

cjd.abstract: Drain-bulk bottom junction capacitance per unit area at zero bias at TNOM. Default = CJS in [Farad/m^2 ].

cjsws.abstract: Source-bulk STI sidewall junction capacitance per unit length at zero bias at TNOM. Default = 5.0 ¡Á 10^-10 in [Farad/m].

cjswd.abstract: Drain-bulk STI sidewall junction capacitance per unit length at zero bias at TNOM. Default = CJSWS in [Farad/m].

cjswgs.abstract: Source-bulk gate-edge sidewall junction capacitance per unit length at zero bias at TNOM. Default = CJSWS in [Farad/m].

cjswgd.abstract: Drain-bulk gate-edge sidewall junction capacitance per unit length at zero bias at TNOM. Default = CJSWGS in [Farad/m].

pbs.abstract: Built-in potential of the source-bulk bottom junction at TNOM. Default = 1.0 in [V].
pbs.notice: PBS(T) reset to 0.01 if PBS  makes it less than 0.01 at a given Temp .

pbd.abstract: Built-in potential of the drain-bulk bottom junction at TNOM. Default = PBS in [V].
pbd.notice: PBD(T) reset to 0.01 if PBD  makes it less than 0.01 at a given Temp .

pbsws.abstract: Built-in potential of the source-bulk STI sidewall junction at TNOM. Default = 1.0 in [V].
pbsws.notice: PBSWS(T) reset to 0.01 if PBSWS makes it less than 0.01 at a given Temp .

pbswd.abstract: Built-in potential of the drain-bulk STI sidewall junction at TNOM. Default = PBSWS in [V].
pbswd.notice: PBSWD(T) reset to 0.01 if PBSWD makes it less than 0.01 at a given Temp .

pbswgs.abstract: Built-in potential of the source-bulk gate-edge junction at TNOM. Default = PBSWS in [V].
pbswgs.notice: PBSWGS(T) reset to 0.01 if PBSWGS makes it less than 0.01 at a given Temp .

pbswgd.abstract: Built-in potential of the drain-bulk gate-edge junction at TNOM. Default = PBSWGS in [V].
pbswgd.notice: PBSWGD(T) reset to 0.01 if PBSWGD makes it less than 0.01 at a given Temp .

tpb.abstract: Temperature-dependence coefficient for PBS and PBD. Default = 0.0 in [V/K].
tpb.notice: PBS(T) reset to 0.01 if TPB makes it less than 0.01 at a given Temp .

tpbsw.abstract: Temperature-dependence coefficient for PBSWS and PBSWD. Default = 0.0 in [V/K].
tpbsw.notice: PBSWS(T) reset to 0.01 if TPBSW makes it less than 0.01 at a given Temp .

tpbswg.abstract: Temperature-dependence coefficient for PBSWGS and PBSWGD. Default = 0.0 in [V/K].
tpbswg.notice: PBSWGS(T) reset to 0.01 if TPBSWG makes it less than 0.01 at a given Temp .

tcj.abstract: Temperature-dependence coefficient for CJS and CJD. Default = 0.0 in [V/K].

tcjsw.abstract: Temperature-dependence coefficient for CJSWS and CJSWD. Default = 0.0 in [V/K].

tcjswg.abstract: Temperature-dependence coefficient for CJSWGS and CJSWGD. Default = 0.0 in [V/K].
